articles.title: New cancer cases to soar 77 percent by 2050, WHO predicts - Al Jazeera English
articles.description: There were an estimated 20 million new cancer cases in 2022, with more than 35 million new cases predicted by 2050.
articles.content:
The number of new cancer cases globally will reach 35 million in 2050, 77 percent higher than the figure in 2022, according to predictions from the World Health Organizations cancer agency.
